  <discussion>Cylindropuntia leptocaulis forms hybrids with C. acanthocarpa var. major (see 3. C.
        ×tetracantha), C. arbuscula, C. fulgida, C. kleiniae, C. spinosior, C. versicolor (see
        discussion under C. ×tetracantha), and C. whipplei. Hybrids in central Arizona have flowers
        intermediate in size to the parents, narrow tuberculate stems bearing 0–1(–2) major spines
        per areole, and tuberculate, spineless, orange to red fruits. The chromosome number reported
        for hybrids is 2n = 22.</discussion>
